# Project context

- **Stack:** React 19, Vite 6, TypeScript, **Matter.js**, **Canvas 2D**, **lucide-react**, **WebSocket** + **OSC** (browser), optional **Node** companion (**ws**, **easymidi**, **tsx**). **Vitest** for tests. No Tailwind, ESLint, Three.js, or path aliases unless added later.

## Styling

- Global layout and tokens live in [src/styles.css](src/styles.css) (CSS variables such as `--panel`, `--accent`, `--text-muted`). UI chrome uses plain CSS classes; the table itself is drawn on a **canvas** in [src/App.tsx](src/App.tsx).

## Imports

- Use **relative** imports from each file (`../shared/...`, `./hooks/...`). There is no `@/*` alias in tsconfig today.

## Import order

When adding or editing imports in `src/**/*.ts` or `src/**/*.tsx`, use **one blank line between groups**; no blank line within a group.

1. **React** — `react`, `react-dom`, `react/*`
2. **External packages** — e.g. `matter-js`, `lucide-react`
3. **Relative** — `./...`, `../...` (hooks, shared, companion)

**`import type`:** group type-only imports last when it improves clarity.

If a module supplies both types and values, one import line is fine; place it by primary use. Keep order readable and consistent with surrounding files.
